Conclusions

Sequence ranking is critical for many CRM applications such as customer churning behavior classiÔ¨Åcation. A major problem for this research is how to resolve
the many sequences which are ambiguous in that they confuse between positive
and negative instances during classiÔ¨Åcation. In this paper, we have presented a
novel method to solving this problem. Our solution is to employ a model based
clustering algorithm and repeated Ô¨Ålter out negative instances that do not contribute to the optimization of the AUC measure.
In the future, we plan to expand the preprocessing component to including
the classiÔ¨Åcation algorithms as well, to consider what the best combination is
for a given classiÔ¨Åcation algorithm. We also plan to test our algorithms for other
multi-dimensional time series data.

