Theories in the social-psychological science indicate that sentiments and emotions of an individual often directly inÔ¨Çuence the individual‚Äôs behavior [1]. Political scientists have postulated hypotheses on how the emotion of a political group
may escalate or deescalate conÔ¨Çicts with opponents and how a political actor may
