Compared to the global model, the ensemble model used in the KNB ranking
method has several advantages:
‚Äì Firstly, training is fast. The time needed for training a learner (e.g. SVM)
often increases nonlinearly with the number of training examples. Training
on separate blocks is a divide-and-conquer strategy and thus is faster.
‚Äì Secondly, test is fast. KNB-based global model must be trained online for
each new query, while local models can be trained oÔ¨Ñine in advance.
‚Äì Thirdly, incremental learning is supported. When a new training block comes,
a new local model can be trained on it and be added into the repository of
local models.
‚Äì Fourthly, a training block can be easily weighted according to its distance
from the test block.
‚Äì Finally, an ensemble model often outperforms a global model in complex
learning problems.

